<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - OIL PAN, VIBRATION DAMPER, OIL
        PUMP, WATER PUMP, AND FRONT COVER - Installation - Oil Pump
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="3">
        <title>Oil Pump</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>When placing the inner and outer gerotor into the oil pump housing, make sure the word "damper" is
                    facing the oil pump housing. Failure to do so will result in engine damage.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1200526" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/eg1441.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Inner Gerotor</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Inner Gerotor</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the inner gerotor over the crankshaft nose with the word "damper" facing out.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200527" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/eg1440.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Outer Gerotor and Square Cut Ring</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Pump Housing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Outer Gerotor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Seal Ring</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the outer gerotor with clean engine oil. Install the gerotor in the oil pump
                housing with the word "damper" facing out.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pack cavities between and around the gerotor with an all purpose assembly grease to insure
                proper priming at engine startup.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the square cut seal ring in the oil pump housing groove.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200528" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/eg1439.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Oil Pump Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the dowel pins and install oil pump housing with seal ring and large gerotor gear onto
                the crankshaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install four oil pump housing mounting bolts. Tighten the bolts to the standard torque
                value.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
